The paper focuses on robotic grasp detection using deep learning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses spatial transformer networks (STN), which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) tasks such as object recognition and image registration. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
